---
alwaysApply: true
---

Before writing any code, you MUST execute these steps in order:

1. `git status` — confirm clean working tree
2. `git checkout -b phase1/<task-name>` — create task branch (use the branch name from the task prompt)
3. If uncommitted changes exist on main, stop and report them before proceeding

During implementation, commit after each logical unit of work:
- `git add <files-in-scope-only>`
- `git commit -m "feat(<task>): <what was done>"`

Never use `git add .` — only stage files listed in your FILE SCOPE.

At task completion, before reporting done:
1. Run all tests
2. Commit any remaining changes
3. Report: branch name, files committed, test results

Never leave work uncommitted. Never commit files outside your FILE SCOPE.
